The Chronicle Chronicle Reporter ZANU-PF is set to hold an Extraordinary Session of the Politburo today at the party headquarters in Harare. In a statement yesterday, ruling party secretary for Information and Publicity Cde Simon Khaya Moyo said: “The Secretary for Administration, Cde Dr O. M Mpofu wishes to advise all Politburo members that there shall be an Extraordinary Session of the Politburo tomorrow, 16 October 2019 at the party headquarters.  All members are to be seated by 11.30 AM.”